{
  "id": "class_0038",
  "name": "Seam-Struck Delver",
  "title_completion": "a Seam-Struck Delver",
  "flavor_text": "The halls are empty now, but the stone remembers every blow. You press your palms to the obsidian walls and feel the old pressures singing back \u2014 coal-dark, brine-soaked, trembling with the weight of what was hewn here. Your magic is not fire, not light, but the slow catastrophic patience of a mountain deciding to move.",
